Stay home to bake with Mom! My mother is a good baker and a great mentor. From pineapple tarts at Chinese New Year to gingerbread men at Christmas, it is our festive tradition, and also a great bonding activity. Baking can be a tedious, labour-intensive process, but also an enriching experience for me. My mother shared her secret tips to make her cakes taste better. She takes an organic culinary approach with no shortcuts. She says that the attention to detail will contribute to the ultimate sensory taste and texture. Through this experience, I also picked up an important life lesson from her – To get the best results, do not take shortcuts. This Mother’s Day, I hope she can rest her battered, covered-in-batter baker hands, take a break from the oven and indulge in @loacker_singapore , which makes a great topping/filling for cakes, cookies and tarts! 👩🏻‍🍳👩‍👧‍👦❤️

Stay home to stay safe! Here is our only chance to be a superhero just by staying at home. Enjoy quarantine time! The best way to stay safe in these times of crisis is to stay at home. Being at home is the ultimate luxury. Happiness is staying at home. I love spending time with my family and dogs! I help my mum to cook delicious meals and do some cleaning. I would like to win Loacker hamper to share with my family. Stay safe, everyone!

Stay home to stay safe and save lives! There is nothing like staying at home for real comfort. Home is where we feel loved, appreciated and safe. It is important to stay away from others when possible, even if we do not have symptoms. It's great to spend quality time with my beloved family. The times I feel most loved are the times I'm near family. The love of family can never be replaced, it's one-of-a-kind. I get to bake cookies with my kids. I get to play interesting games with them! We share stories before bedtime. It's great! Keep calm and stay at home, everyone! Hope to win a Loacker hamper to enjoy the moment! My grandkids will love it! Of course, my heart goes to the victims of the tragic event! I hope everyone is doing well! I would like to thank the front liners for their great effort and sacrifice. THANK YOU!
